-align: -0.838ex; width:27.219ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle ({=
-a})/b=3D{-(a/b)}=3Da/({-b})}"></span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modulo#cite_note-6"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up><sup id=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Modulo#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Notation">Notation</h2><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DModulo&amp;action=3D=
edit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Notation"><span>edit</span></a=
><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
This section is about the binary <i>mod</i> operation. For the <i>(mod</i> =
m<i>)</i> notation, see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congruence=
_relation" title=3D"Congruence relation">congruence relation</a>.</div>
<p>Some calculators have a <span class=3D"texhtml">mod()</span> function bu=
tton, and many programming languages have a similar function, expressed as =
<span class=3D"texhtml">mod(<i>a</i>, <i>n</i>)</span>, for example. Some a=
lso support expressions that use "%", "mod", or "Mod" as a modulo or remain=
der <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operator_(programming)" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Operator (programming)">operator</a>, such as <co=
de class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-text mw-content-ltr" style=3D"" =
dir=3D"ltr">a&nbsp;% n</code> or <code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-l=
ang-text mw-content-ltr" style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">a mod n</code>.
</p><p>For environments lacking a similar function, any of the three defini=
tions above can be used.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Common_pitfalls">Common pit=
falls</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DModulo=
&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Common pitfalls"=
><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span=
></div>
<p>When the result of a modulo operation has the sign of the dividend (trun=
cated definition), it can lead to surprising mistakes.
</p><p>For example, to test if an integer is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Parity_(mathematics)" title=3D"Parity (mathematics)">odd</a>, on=
e might be inclined to test if the remainder by 2 is equal to 1:
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-cpp mw-content-ltr" dir=3D"ltr=
"><pre><span></span><span class=3D"kt">bool</span><span class=3D"w"> </span=
><span class=3D"nf">is_odd</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"k=
t">int</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">n</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">)</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"p">{</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"k">return</span><span class=3D"=
w"> </span><span class=3D"n">n</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=
=3D"o">%</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"mi">2</span><span c=
lass=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"o">=3D=3D</span><span class=3D"w"> </span=
><span class=3D"mi">1</span><span class=3D"p">;</span>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>
</pre></div>
<p>But in a language where modulo has the sign of the dividend, that is inc=
orrect, because when <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i></span> (the dividend)=
 is negative and odd, <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i></span> mod 2 returns=
 =E2=88=921, and the function returns false.
</p><p>One correct alternative is to test that the remainder is not 0 (beca=
use remainder 0 is the same regardless of the signs):
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-cpp mw-content-ltr" dir=3D"ltr=
"><pre><span></span><span class=3D"kt">bool</span><span class=3D"w"> </span=
><span class=3D"nf">is_odd</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"k=
t">int</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">n</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">)</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"p">{</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"k">return</span><span class=3D"=
w"> </span><span class=3D"n">n</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=
=3D"o">%</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"mi">2</span><span c=
lass=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"o">!=3D</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><=
span class=3D"mi">0</span><span class=3D"p">;</span>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>
</pre></div>
<p>Or with the binary arithmetic:
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-cpp mw-content-ltr" dir=3D"ltr=
"><pre><span></span><span class=3D"kt">bool</span><span class=3D"w"> </span=
><span class=3D"nf">is_odd</span><span class=3D"p">(</span><span class=3D"k=
t">int</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"n">n</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">)</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"p">{</span>
<span class=3D"w">    </span><span class=3D"k">return</span><span class=3D"=
w"> </span><span class=3D"n">n</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=
=3D"o">&amp;</span><span class=3D"w"> </span><span class=3D"mi">1</span><sp=
an class=3D"p">;</span>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>
</pre></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Performance_issues">Perform=
ance issues</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
Modulo&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Performanc=
e issues"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</sp=
an></span></div>
<p>Modulo operations might be implemented such that a division with a remai=
nder is calculated each time. For special cases, on some hardware, faster a=
lternatives exist. For example, the modulo of <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Powers_of_2" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Powers of 2">powers=
 of 2</a> can alternatively be expressed as a <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Bitwise_operation" title=3D"Bitwise operation">bitwise</a> AND =
operation (assuming <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i></span> is a positive i=
nteger, or using a non-truncating definition):
</p>
<dl><dd><code>x&nbsp;% 2<sup>n</sup> =3D=3D x &amp; (2<sup>n</sup> - 1)</co=
de></dd></dl>
<p>Examples:
</p>
<dl><dd><code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-text mw-content-ltr" =
style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">x&nbsp;% 2 =3D=3D x &amp; 1</code></dd>
<dd><code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-text mw-content-ltr" styl=
e=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">x&nbsp;% 4 =3D=3D x &amp; 3</code></dd>
<dd><code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-text mw-content-ltr" styl=
e=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">x&nbsp;% 8 =3D=3D x &amp; 7</code></dd></dl>
<p>In devices and software that implement bitwise operations more efficient=
ly than modulo, these alternative forms can result in faster calculations.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Modulo#cite_note-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compiler_optimization" clas=
s=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Compiler optimization">Compiler optimizations</a=
> may recognize expressions of the form <code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-high=
light-lang-text mw-content-ltr" style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">expression&nbsp;% co=
nstant</code> where <code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-text mw-c=
ontent-ltr" style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">constant</code> is a power of two and au=
tomatically implement them as <code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang=
-text mw-content-ltr" style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">expression &amp; (constant-1)<=
/code>, allowing the programmer to write clearer code without compromising =
performance. This simple optimization is not possible for languages in whic=
h the result of the modulo operation has the sign of the dividend (includin=
g <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C_(programming_language)" title=
=3D"C (programming language)">C</a>), unless the dividend is of an <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Signedness" title=3D"Signedness">unsigned=
</a> integer type. This is because, if the dividend is negative, the modulo=
 will be negative, whereas <code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-te=
xt mw-content-ltr" style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">expression &amp; (constant-1)</co=
de> will always be positive. For these languages, the equivalence <code>x&n=
bsp;% 2<sup>n</sup> =3D=3D x &lt; 0&nbsp;? x | ~(2<sup>n</sup> - 1)&nbsp;: =
x &amp; (2<sup>n</sup> - 1)</code> has to be used instead, expressed using =
bitwise OR, NOT and AND operations.
</p><p>Optimizations for general constant-modulus operations also exist by =
calculating the division first using the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Division_algorithm#Division_by_a_constant" title=3D"Division algorit=
hm">constant-divisor optimization</a>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Properties_(identities)"><s=
pan id=3D"Properties_.28identities.29"></span>Properties (identities)</h2><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</spa=
n><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DModulo&amp;action=
=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: Properties (identities)"><s=
pan>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></=
div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
See also: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_arithmetic#Prope=
rties" title=3D"Modular arithmetic">Modular arithmetic =C2=A7&nbsp;Properti=
es</a></div>
<p>Some modulo operations can be factored or expanded similarly to other ma=
thematical operations. This may be useful in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Cryptography" title=3D"Cryptography">cryptography</a> proofs, su=
ch as the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diffie%E2%80%93Hellman_k=
ey_exchange" title=3D"Diffie=E2=80=93Hellman key exchange">Diffie=E2=80=93H=
ellman key exchange</a>. The properties involving multiplication, division,=
 and exponentiation generally require that <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a</i>=
</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i></span> are integers.
</p>
<ul><li>Identity:
<ul><li><span class=3D"texhtml">(<i>a</i> mod <i>n</i>) mod <i>n</i> =3D <i=
>a</i> mod <i>n</i></span>.</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i><sup><i>x</i></sup> mod <i>n</i> =3D 0<=
/span> for all positive integer values of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i><=
/span>.</li>
<li>If <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>p</i></span> is a <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number" title=3D"Prime number">prime number</a> whi=
ch is not a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Divisor" title=3D"Divi=
sor">divisor</a> of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i></span>, then <span cla=
ss=3D"texhtml"><i>ab</i><span style=3D"padding-left:0.12em;"><sup><i>p</i>=
=E2=88=921</sup></span> mod <i>p</i> =3D <i>a</i> mod <i>p</i></span>, due =
to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fermat%27s_little_theorem" titl=
e=3D"Fermat's little theorem">Fermat's little theorem</a>.</li></ul></li>
<li>Inverse:
<ul><li><span class=3D"texhtml">[(=E2=88=92<i>a</i> mod <i>n</i>) + (<i>a</=
i> mod <i>n</i>)] mod <i>n</i> =3D 0</span>.</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><sup>=E2=88=921</sup> mod <i>n</i></spa=
n> denotes the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_multiplicat=
ive_inverse" title=3D"Modular multiplicative inverse">modular multiplicativ=
e inverse</a>, which is defined <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/If=
_and_only_if" title=3D"If and only if">if and only if</a> <span class=3D"te=
xhtml"><i>b</i></span> and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i></span> are <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Relatively_prime" class=3D"mw-redirect=
" title=3D"Relatively prime">relatively prime</a>, which is the case when t=
he left hand side is defined: <span class=3D"texhtml">[(<i>b</i><sup>=E2=88=
=921</sup> mod <i>n</i>)(<i>b</i> mod <i>n</i>)] mod <i>n</i> =3D 1</span>.=
</li></ul></li>
<li>Distributive:
<ul><li><span class=3D"texhtml">(<i>a</i> + <i>b</i>) mod <i>n</i> =3D [(<i=
>a</i> mod <i>n</i>) + (<i>b</i> mod <i>n</i>)] mod <i>n</i></span>.</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml"><i>ab</i> mod <i>n</i> =3D [(<i>a</i> mod <i>n<=
/i>)(<i>b</i> mod <i>n</i>)] mod <i>n</i></span>.</li></ul></li>
<li>Division (definition):  <span class=3D"texhtml"><span class=3D"sfrac">=
=E2=81=A0<span class=3D"tion"><span class=3D"num"><i>a</i></span><span clas=
s=3D"sr-only">/</span><span class=3D"den"><i>b</i></span></span>=E2=81=A0</=
span> mod <i>n</i> =3D [(<i>a</i> mod <i>n</i>)(<i>b</i><sup>=E2=88=921</su=
p> mod <i>n</i>)] mod <i>n</i></span>, when the right hand side is defined =
(that is when <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i></span> and <span class=3D"te=
xhtml"><i>n</i></span> are <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coprime=
" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Coprime">coprime</a>), and undefined other=
wise.</li>
<li>Inverse multiplication:  <span class=3D"texhtml">[(<i>ab</i> mod <i>n</=
i>)(<i>b</i><sup>=E2=88=921</sup> mod <i>n</i>)] mod <i>n</i> =3D <i>a</i> =
mod <i>n</i></span>.</li></ul>
