<p>In addition, many computer systems provide a <code class=3D"mw-highlight=
 mw-highlight-lang-text mw-content-ltr" style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">divmod</code=
> functionality, which produces the quotient and the remainder at the same =
time. Examples include the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X86_arc=
hitecture" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"X86 architecture">x86 architectur=
e</a>'s <code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-text mw-content-ltr" =
style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">IDIV</code> instruction, the C programming language'=
s <code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-text mw-content-ltr" style=
=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">div()</code> function, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)" title=3D"Python (programming lang=
uage)">Python</a>'s <code class=3D"mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-text mw-c=
ontent-ltr" style=3D"" dir=3D"ltr">divmod()</code> function.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Generalizations">Generaliza=
tions</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DModulo=
&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: Generalizations"=
><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span=
></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Modulo_with_offset">Modulo =
with offset</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
Modulo&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit section: Modulo wit=
h offset"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</sp=
an></span></div>
<p>Sometimes it is useful for the result of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" st=
yle=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span> modulo <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" sty=
le=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> to lie not between 0 and <span class=3D"=
texhtml"><i>n</i> =E2=88=92 1</span>, but between some number <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">d</span> and <span class=3D"=
texhtml"><i>d</i> + <i>n</i> =E2=88=92 1</span>. In that case, <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">d</span> is called an <i>off=
set</i> and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>d</i> =3D 1</span> is particularly c=
ommon.=20
</p><p>There does not seem to be a standard notation for this operation, so=
 let us tentatively use <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a</i> mod<sub><i>d</i></=
sub> <i>n</i></span>. We thus have the following definition:<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-Mathematica_Mod_66-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Modulo#cite_note-Mathematica_Mod-66"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>60<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <span class=
=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> =3D <i>a</i> mod<sub><i>d</i></sub> <i>n</i></span> j=
ust in case <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>d</i> =E2=89=A4 <i>x</i> =E2=89=A4 <=
i>d</i> + <i>n</i> =E2=88=92 1</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> =
mod <i>n</i> =3D <i>a</i> mod <i>n</i></span>. Clearly, the usual modulo op=
eration corresponds to zero offset: <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a</i> mod <i=
>n</i> =3D <i>a</i> mod<sub>0</sub> <i>n</i></span>.=20
</p><p>The operation of modulo with offset is related to the <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Floor_and_ceiling_functions" title=3D"Floor and =
ceiling functions">floor function</a> as follows:
</p>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><s=
pan class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display:=
 none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\dis=
playstyle a\operatorname {mod} _{d}n=3Da-n\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\rig=
ht\rfloor .}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>a</mi>
        <msub>
          <mi>mod</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>d</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8A</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mfrac>
              <mrow>
                <mi>a</mi>
                <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                <mi>d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>n</mi>
            </mfrac>
          </mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8B</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle a\operatornam=
e {mod} _{d}n=3Da-n\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor .}</annotatio=
n>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/2295c23019fdd9ab8984f08bc8919006923080fd" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.505ex; width:27.699ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle a\=
operatorname {mod} _{d}n=3Da-n\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor .}=
"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<p>To see this, let <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline=
"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"disp=
lay: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{=
\textstyle x=3Da-n\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8A</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mfrac>
              <mrow>
                <mi>a</mi>
                <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                <mi>d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>n</mi>
            </mfrac>
          </mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8B</mo>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\textstyle x=3Da-n\left\lfl=
oor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/cecb12b97c06c7fec21b9f083c9922f75b323b3f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:16.579ex; height:4.843ex;" alt=3D"{\textstyle x=3Da=
-n\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor }"></span>. We first show that=
 <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> mod <i>n</i> =3D <i>a</i> mod <i>n</i></s=
pan>. It is in general true that <span class=3D"texhtml">(<i>a</i> + <i>bn<=
/i>) mod <i>n</i> =3D <i>a</i> mod <i>n</i></span> for all integers <span c=
lass=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span>; thus, this is =
true also in the particular case when <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-m=
ath-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a=
11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Ma=
thML" alttext=3D"{\textstyle b=3D-\!\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfl=
oor }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>b</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mspace width=3D"negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8A</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mfrac>
              <mrow>
                <mi>a</mi>
                <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                <mi>d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>n</mi>
            </mfrac>
          </mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8B</mo>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\textstyle b=3D-\!\left\lfl=
oor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/5cf3e6789718c0a36c6b0aae5dbe04b93f08f941" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:12.203ex; height:4.843ex;" alt=3D"{\textstyle b=3D-=
\!\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor }"></span>; but that means tha=
t <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"m=
we-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math =
xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\textstyle x{\bmod=
 {n}}=3D\left(a-n\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor \right)\!{\bmod=
 {n}}=3Da{\bmod {n}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mo lspace=3D"thickmathspace" rspace=3D"thickmathspace">mod</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <mi>a</mi>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mrow>
              <mo>=E2=8C=8A</mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mfrac>
                  <mrow>
                    <mi>a</mi>
                    <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                    <mi>d</mi>
                  </mrow>
                  <mi>n</mi>
                </mfrac>
              </mrow>
              <mo>=E2=8C=8B</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width=3D"negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mo lspace=3D"thickmathspace" rspace=3D"thickmathspace">mod</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mo lspace=3D"thickmathspace" rspace=3D"thickmathspace">mod</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\textstyle x{\bmod {n}}=3D\=
left(a-n\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor \right)\!{\bmod {n}}=3Da=
{\bmod {n}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/55dbae6aaf1928432910a9a06191e870c3cf228c" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:44.911ex; height:4.843ex;" alt=3D"{\textstyle x{\bm=
od {n}}=3D\left(a-n\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor \right)\!{\bm=
od {n}}=3Da{\bmod {n}}}"></span>, which is what we wanted to prove. It rema=
ins to be shown that <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>d</i> =E2=89=A4 <i>x</i> =
=E2=89=A4 <i>d</i> + <i>n</i> =E2=88=92 1</span>. Let <span class=3D"texhtm=
l mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">k</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mv=
ar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">r</span> be the integers such that <span c=
lass=3D"texhtml"><i>a</i> =E2=88=92 <i>d</i> =3D <i>kn</i> + <i>r</i></span=
> with <span class=3D"texhtml">0 =E2=89=A4 <i>r</i> =E2=89=A4 <i>n</i> =E2=
=88=92 1</span> (see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_div=
ision" title=3D"Euclidean division">Euclidean division</a>). Then <span cla=
ss=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mat=
hml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"ht=
tp://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\textstyle \left\lfloor {\fra=
c {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor =3Dk}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8A</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mfrac>
              <mrow>
                <mi>a</mi>
                <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                <mi>d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>n</mi>
            </mfrac>
          </mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8B</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>k</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\textstyle \left\lfloor {\f=
rac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor =3Dk}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/c7588602c0a11bb9742f4c6edf3c740a1b55dd0f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:10.609ex; height:4.843ex;" alt=3D"{\textstyle \left=
\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor =3Dk}"></span>, thus <span class=3D"m=
we-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inl=
ine mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://ww=
w.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\textstyle x=3Da-n\left\lfloor {\fra=
c {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor =3Da-nk=3Dd+r}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8A</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mfrac>
              <mrow>
                <mi>a</mi>
                <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                <mi>d</mi>
              </mrow>
              <mi>n</mi>
            </mfrac>
          </mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8B</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mi>k</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>d</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>r</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\textstyle x=3Da-n\left\lfl=
oor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor =3Da-nk=3Dd+r}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/1d428438128efb6d26627bf91adfaeca82b1a743" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:34.557ex; height:4.843ex;" alt=3D"{\textstyle x=3Da=
-n\left\lfloor {\frac {a-d}{n}}\right\rfloor =3Da-nk=3Dd+r}"></span>. Now t=
ake <span class=3D"texhtml">0 =E2=89=A4 <i>r</i> =E2=89=A4 <i>n</i> =E2=88=
=92 1</span> and add <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:itali=
c;">d</span> to both sides, obtaining <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>d</i> =E2=
=89=A4 <i>d</i> + <i>r</i> =E2=89=A4 <i>d</i> + <i>n</i> =E2=88=92 1</span>=
. But we've seen that <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> =3D <i>d</i> + <i>r<=
/i></span>, so we are done.
</p><p>The modulo with offset <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>a</i> mod<sub><i>d=
